column4: I have a question. Will uninstalling gnome-session mess anything up? I don't want to use fallback mode anymore, and I'm having issues with nautilus so i was planning on uninstalling both of those. Will this break Unity or GNOME Shell?
I do, but I don't use it. I use GNOME Shell for everything.
Will uninstalling nautilus or gnome-session (which seems to want to uninstall when I try deleting nautilus) hurt my computer?
